page.title: 11Marnhull,Demography,Cubs.
page.content: About 13% of the inhabitants were actually born in Marnhull.19% come from other parts of Dorset.Some were born abroad,leaving 64% from other parts of the British Isles.Apart from those born in neighbouring counties, a large number come from London and the Home Counties,many to retire. Of CHILDREN,the numbers born in and outside Dorset are about the same,but less than one third were born in Marnhull. During the last 16 years a number of small housing estates have been built in Marnhull.The houses have been bought by people from outside Marnhull thereby altering its demography. CUBS,a boys'uniformed organisation, meet every Wednesday.First we have the Grand Howl,flag break,register and uniform inpection.Games or tracking are followed by group activities.
